 President
Muhammadu Buhari Thursday expressed sadness over the passing of retired
Ambassador Ado Sanusi, the Dan Iyan Kano and uncle to Emir of Kano,
Muhammadu Sanusi II. The President described the late Ado Sanusi “as a
distinguished diplomat and remarkable statesman who had served his country and
his immediate community with dedication.” According to him, “the great contributions of the late
diplomat would be remembered for many years to come.” President Buhari also extended condolences to the Emir of Kano,
his family, the Kano State Government and the people of the State at large over
“this enormous loss of a remarkable gentleman and committed public
servant.”